sentences: Ethan Thomas Robert Johns (born 1969 in Merton, London, England) is an English record producer, engineer, mixer, songwriter, and multi-instrumentalist.
In 2012, he won the Brit Award for Best British Producer.
Johns released his debut solo album Independent Years (1991) followed by If Not Now Then When on vinyl in November 2012, which was later released in other formats in February 2013.

Johns spent 15 years in Los Angeles as a record producer and musician, but currently lives and continues to make records in England.
